summary: WHEN DRIVING, THE LOW BEAM HEADLIGHTS ARE EXTREMELY DIM,  ESPECIALLY AT NIGHT .  IT IS VERY DIFFICULT TO EVEN TELL IF THEY ARE ON.  HIGH BEAMS ARE FINE.
